The paper focuses on the hardware implementation of activation functions in neural networks, which falls under the intersection of computer architecture (cs.AR), electronic circuits and systems (cs.ET), neural networks (cs.NE), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the design and optimization of combinational circuits for activation functions, which is a topic that is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
